  "texts": [
    "Humans are the only species whose members have an awareness of themselves as embodying a unique, collectively structured form of life.",
    "The fact that culture accumulates over historical time has exerted remarkable effects on humans' understanding of self and other.",
    "There appears to be a sharp division between species whose culture 'ratchets up' in the way human culture does, and others, whose behavioural patterns are not preserved across generations.",
    "Importantly, with the dawn of cultural evolutionary processes, humans developed a consciousness of themselves as being part of a community whose members are interdependent in their learning (Moll & Kern, 2020; Moll, 2020).",
